  "market_context": "Bitcoin was consolidating between three key horizontal zones on the daily chart: a clear upper resistance, a clear lower support, and a middle zone with multiple tests. The market eventually broke the upper resistance decisively, triggering a strong bull run.",
  "key_observation": "The analyst emphasized that strong, clear bounces (not just numerous touches) define high-probability support/resistance levels; the middle zone gained validity after two strong resistance reactions and two smaller support tests.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Zoom out on the daily BTCUSDT chart to identify only the most obvious, widely visible support and resistance zones.",
    "Step 2: Evaluate each zone by strength of reaction—not number of touches—highlighting the upper resistance (multiple strong rejections) and lower support (strong bounce + repeated buyer intervention).",
    "Step 3: Assess the middle zone: initially weak, but included after observing two strong resistance reactions and two smaller support tests, meeting the analyst’s threshold for validity.",
    "Step 4: Observe how price tested the middle zone repeatedly as resistance, including a large wick rejection, before finally breaking above both the middle zone and the upper resistance.",
    "Step 5: Note that the breakout above the key resistance triggered strong follow-through buying, marking the start of a major Bitcoin bull run."
  ],
  "outcome": "Bullish breakout above key resistance led to a sustained upward move; the analyst identifies this as the beginning of the Bitcoin bull run.",
  "lessons": "Strong, decisive price reactions at a level matter more than the count of touches; drawing zones (not lines) better reflects real market behavior; breakouts from well-defined resistance can initiate major trends.",
